sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant C as Client
  participant API as API Service
  participant PG as Postgres
  participant Q as Queue (arq/Redis)
  participant W as Worker pool
  participant S as Redis semaphore (cap 90)
  participant ASR as ASR vendor
  participant D as Deid svc (CIPHER)

  C->>API: POST /transcribe {6 chunk paths, userId}
  API->>PG: TX insert job(PENDING) + 6 chunks(PENDING)
  API->>Q: enqueue 6 chunk tasks
  API-->>C: 202 {jobId}   (t ≈ 10ms)

  par 6 chunks fan out in parallel
    Q->>W: chunk task
    W->>S: acquire permit (TTL lease 30s)
    W->>ASR: GET /get-asr-output?path=...
    ASR-->>W: 200 transcript (5–10s)
    W->>S: release permit
    W->>PG: chunk → COMPLETED + text
  and one chunk hits the 1/20 transient failure
    W->>ASR: GET /get-asr-output?path=chunk-4
    ASR-->>W: 500
    W->>S: release permit
    Note over W: backoff ~1s + jitter, attempt 2/4
    W->>S: re-acquire permit
    W->>ASR: retry chunk-4
    ASR-->>W: 200 transcript
    W->>PG: chunk → COMPLETED
  end

  W->>PG: last chunk terminal → claim stitch
  W->>W: concat in ordinal order
  W->>D: POST stitched text
  D-->>W: BIO spans (~50ms) → mask [NAME] [DATE] [MRN]
  W->>PG: job → COMPLETED, transcript_deid, completedTime

  loop client polls
    C->>API: GET /transcript/{jobId}
    API->>PG: read
    API-->>C: TranscriptResult (deid by default)
  end

  Note over C,D: happy path ≈ 10s · with one retry ≈ 20s · budget met
